items.name: 国画 Chinese Painting | 水墨江南(Ink Jiangnan)
items.description:
国画 | 水墨江南

你一句春不晚，我就到了真江南! 在你的笔下，我也窥见雪山，也听檐下雨落在某块你轻盈踏过的石上，有风轻喃。若你向前走着，我只顾跟上撑伞，再越过几座桥，浑不知衣袖已淋湿一半，你一句天色不晚，我就到过真江南。

画里的水墨江南，白墙黑瓦空灵清丽，意境甚美，令人陶醉，不知所往，安安静静地看，有韵味，有回响，或许你是在看景，或许你是在想江南的她，或许~

模型简介

创作灵感来自于吴冠中老师的作品，江南水乡，白白的墙，黑黑的瓦，初看不喜欢，再看出不来，喜欢~~

希望你也有属于自己的江南。

实践

触发词： QIEM6NCN

Lora值：0.6~0.8

相关提示词： house, river, white wall，boat, flower等等；

其他参考提示词：chinese ink painting,chinese style等等；

出图尺寸： 1024x1480 或者 1480x1024，更大的都可以。

喜欢的朋友，可以停下脚步，享受江南时光。

=======================================================================

Chinese Painting | Ink Jiangnan

If you say that spring is not too late, I will be in the real south of the Yangtze River! In your writing, I can see the snow-capped mountains, and I can hear the rain falling on a certain rock you lightly stepped on, and the wind murmurs softly. If you walk forward, I just keep up with the umbrella and cross a few bridges. I don’t know that my sleeves are half wet. If you say that it’s not too late, I’ve been to the real Jiangnan.

The ink and wash Jiangnan in the painting, the white walls and black tiles are ethereal and beautiful, the artistic conception is very beautiful, it is intoxicating, you don’t know where you are going, you look at it quietly, there is charm and echo, maybe you are looking at the scenery, maybe you are thinking about Jiangnan her, maybe~

Model Introduction

The creative inspiration comes from the works of Mr. Wu Guanzhong, Jiangnan water town, white walls, black and black tiles, I don’t like it at first glance, but I can’t see it anymore, I like it~~

I hope you also have your own Jiangnan.

practice

Other reference prompt words: chinese ink painting, chinese style, etc.;

Friends who like it can stop and enjoy the time in Jiangnan.

items.description:
国画 | 没骨画-花卉篇

迄今可见的关于没骨画最早的记载为宋代郭若虚的《图画见闻志》，徐崇嗣画没骨图,以其先笔墨骨气而名之,但收取浓丽生态以定品。

只有中国才有的画风。

模型简介

汇集了花卉，蝴蝶类的没骨画作品作为训练集，作品量比较少，在丰富度上有欠缺；

自己摸索炼丹，技能拙劣，还在探索中，希望道友们多多指点。

实践

1. lora值：0.6~0.8

2. 基础模型：SDXL 1.0

3. 触发词：mogu-painting

欢迎各位道友入座指正点评，学习交流。

============================================================

Chinese Painting | Boneless Painting - Floral Series

The earliest recorded mention of boneless painting can be found in the "Tu Hua Jian Wen Zhi" by Guo Ruoxu of the Song dynasty. Xu Chongsi created boneless paintings, known for their initial bold and vigorous strokes, yet capturing rich and vibrant eclecticism to define their essence.

A painting style unique to China.

Model Introduction

This model gathers boneless painting works featuring flowers and butterflies as the training dataset, though the quantity of works is limited, resulting in some deficiency in diversity.

I'm experimenting and refining my skills in the realm of alchemy, with modest proficiency and ongoing exploration. I warmly welcome guidance from fellow practitioners.

Practice

  1. Lora Value: 0.6~0.8

  2. Base Model: SDXL 1.0

  3. Trigger Word: mogu-painting

Welcome all fellow practitioners to take a seat, offer corrections and comments, and engage in a collaborative learning experience.

items.name: Shouta Magatsuchi (Miss Kobayashi's Dragon Maid / 小林さんちのメイドラゴ)
items.description:
Trigger word "shouta".

If you suspected that lucoa would inevitably follow along then you would be correct. She can be summoned with an alchemy circle, a cauldron and the keyword "lucoa" but I highly recommend against trying to gen both characters at once or their identifiable properties are almost guaranteed to get mixed up in the teleporter.

This is my first attempt at making a LoRA. I noticed many available (of varying degrees of ease of use) for other characters in this show, and wanted to take a stab at this one as well.

If mood is up to it, I might further refine this LoRA (largely trying to better clean up the training set of tags might help .. also does anyone know how to fold undesired output back into the training process as examples of what not to do? lol!) and/or might take a stab at some other under-represented characters from maiddragon like Saikawa, Takiya, or Georgie?

What I have put a lot of effort into however was correcting "Xboys / Xgirls" tags auto-detected wrongly on 90% of photos because DeepBooru was convinced that Shouta must be a girl. >.<

That said, generating with this LoRA still has a high chance of making characters that look a lot like Shouta but who are female and of arbitrary ages and heights. Or of mixing characteristics from different characters in the show, most notably trying to put Lucoa's horns or baseball cap onto Shouta's head entirely unasked for. u.u Using "1boy" seems to do a great job at clarifying his gender though, as does describing the character in English language as long as there are no other characters in the scene.

items.description:
Steampunk style LoRA for SDXL 1.0.

This LoRA does not require a trigger word, but you can add "steampunk" as well as associated concepts to enhance the effect.

Steampunk is a genre of science fiction and fantasy that blends Victorian-era technology with elements of fantasy and steam-powered machinery. Some concepts associated with steampunk include:

1. Steam-powered technology: The use of steam engines, airships, and other machines powered by steam to create energy or transportation.
2. Victorian-era fashion: The look and style of clothing worn during the Victorian era, which often featured ornate details and fabrics.
3. Mechanical devices: Devices that are powered by steam or other forms of energy, such as clocks, gears, and automatons.
4. Steampunk literature: Books, comics, and other media that feature stories set in a world where steampunk technology exists.
5. Steampunk fashion: Clothing inspired by the look and feel of Victorian-era fashion, often featuring metal studs, chains, and other embellishments.

items.name: Airfuck's Brute Mix
items.description:
Airfuck's Brute Mix (ABM)

Model development is a lot of work. Beer makes it easier 🍺😘

This beginner-friendly model is great at generating male-focused scenes. Men tend to be muscular by default and the model likes to reveal dicks and asses - so be prepared to see some dicks even if you did not prompt for them.

You can achieve a variety of body types, poses and even sexual acts by prompting accordingly. The style has a brute touch to it: Men tend to be masculine, raunchy and rough. Images look gritty, muscles and dicks are often huge. Use the prompt if you wish to tone that down or exaggerate it even further. This model is not suited for women because they tend to grow dicks. You have been warned!

Compared to my Airfuck's Wild Mix this one is a little bit less responsive to your prompt and also a little less versatile (prove me wrong!). The HDR style might go over the top for some of your images. On the plus side it is really good for large dicks and also handles groups of men quite well. The model is very sexual and although it still struggles with sexual position (especially when more then two people are involved), you can get lucky with lewd pics pretty often.

Tips for model usage

Simple and short prompts without the usual "incantations" (like "masterpiece, 4k, ...") can bring you a long way. Also try to be light on the negatives, only include them if you can't achieve your desired look otherwise. Beware of negative textual embeddings - they may change style and content considerably.

The model likes to reveal dicks. If you find they are of weird shape, try to explicitly include penis in the prompt or move it further up in the prompt. Flaccid dicks are a bit harder to generate: Try to use flaccid without "penis" in the positives and erection in the negatives. Realistic or even small dick sizes are still problematic. You shouldn't need LoRAs for generating convincing junk though. The model is still compatible to a wide range of LoRAs if you wish to use them.

The model defaults to masculine guys. Prompt accordingly to prevent that. Use beefy to fatten up your guys (this is different than my Airfuck's Wild Mix!).

Settings that work well are:

  • Sampling Method: DPM++ SDE Karras

  • Sampling Steps: ⪰ 20

  • CFG Scale: between 5 and 7 (don't go too high here)

I usually use resolutions between 512x512 and 768x768 and upscale using the following settings - feel free to change if you have a beefier GPU:

  • Restore faces: on

  • Hires. fix: on

  • Upscaler: R-ESRGAN 4x+

  • Hires steps: 10

  • Denoising strength: 0.5

  • Upscale by: 1.5

I also recommend the Face Editor and ADetailer extensions for Automatic1111 - the latter becomes especially useful with the penis refiner model.

Credits

Following models are in the mix:

  • Airfuck's Wild Mix

  • Unstable Homoerotic Diffusion (UHD)

  • Boyfusion

Thanks to all data taggers, model trainers and creators, and Open Source Stable Diffusion enthusiasts - without you none of this would be possible!

Also thanks to all the nice people in the Unstable Diffusion Discord #men-only channel. Your feedback, ideas, prompts and company are invaluable! 🥰

items.name: hoshino/小鳥遊ホシノ/星野 (Blue Archive)
items.description:
• THIS MODEL HAS TWO FILES. YOU NEED TO USE THEM TOGETHER!!!
  • The associated trigger words are only for reference, it may need to be adjusted at some times.
  • The recommended weight for the embedding model is 1, which provides higher fidelity; if greater generalization is needed, it can be lowered to 0.5. The recommended weight for the LoRA model is 0.85.

How to Use This Model

THIS MODEL HAS TWO FILES. YOU NEED TO USE THEM TOGETHER!!!. In this case, you need to download both hoshino_bluearchive.pt and hoshino_bluearchive.safetensors, then use hoshino_bluearchive.pt as texture inversion embedding, and use hoshino_bluearchive.safetensors as LoRA at the same time.

このモデルには2つのファイルがあります。一緒に使う必要があります！！！。 この場合、hoshino_bluearchive.ptとhoshino_bluearchive.safetensorsの両方をダウンロード する必要があります。hoshino_bluearchive.ptをテクスチャ反転埋め込みとして使用し、同時にhoshino_bluearchive.safetensorsをLoRAとして使用してください。

这个模型有两个文件。你需要同时使用它们！！！。 在这种情况下，您需要下载hoshino_bluearchive.pt和hoshino_bluearchive.safetensors这两个文件，然后将hoshino_bluearchive.pt用作纹理反转嵌入， 同时使用hoshino_bluearchive.safetensors作为LoRA。

이 모델은 두 개의 파일이 있습니다. 두 파일을 함께 사용해야 합니다!!!. 이 경우에는 hoshino_bluearchive.pt와 hoshino_bluearchive.safetensors 두 파일을 모두 다운로드하신 다음에 hoshino_bluearchive.pt을 텍스처 반전 임베딩으로 사용하고, 동시에 hoshino_bluearchive.safetensors을 LoRA로 사용하셔야 합니다.

(Translated with ChatGPT)

The trigger word is hoshino_bluearchive, and the recommended tags are best quality, masterpiece, highres, solo, {hoshino_bluearchive:1.15}, ahoge, pink_hair, long_hair, halo, bangs, blue_eyes, very_long_hair, yellow_eyes, heterochromia, open_mouth, blush, hair_between_eyes, smile, fang, necktie.

How This Model Is Trained

This model is trained with HCP-Diffusion. And the auto-training framework is maintained by DeepGHS Team.

Why Some Preview Images Not Look Like Hoshino Bluearchive

All the prompt texts used on the preview images (which can be viewed by clicking on the images) are automatically generated using clustering algorithms based on feature information extracted from the training dataset. The seed used during image generation is also randomly generated, and the images have not undergone any selection or modification. As a result, there is a possibility of the mentioned issues occurring.

In practice, based on our internal testing, most models that experience such issues perform better in actual usage than what is seen in the preview images. The only thing you may need to do is adjusting the tags you are using.

I Felt This Model May Be Overfitting or Underfitting, What Shall I Do

Our model has been published on huggingface repository - CyberHarem/hoshino_bluearchive, where models of all the steps are saved. Also, we published the training dataset on huggingface dataset - CyberHarem/hoshino_bluearchive, which may be helpful to you.

Why Not Just Using The Better-Selected Images

Our model's entire process, from data crawling, training, to generating preview images and publishing, is 100% automated without any human intervention. It's an interesting experiment conducted by our team, and for this purpose, we have developed a complete set of software infrastructure, including data filtering, automatic training, and automated publishing. Therefore, if possible, we would appreciate more feedback or suggestions as they are highly valuable to us.

Why Can't the Desired Character Outfits Be Accurately Generated

Our current training data is sourced from various image websites, and for a fully automated pipeline, it's challenging to accurately predict which official images a character possesses. Consequently, outfit generation relies on clustering based on labels from the training dataset in an attempt to achieve the best possible recreation. We will continue to address this issue and attempt optimization, but it remains a challenge that cannot be completely resolved. The accuracy of outfit recreation is also unlikely to match the level achieved by manually trained models.

In fact, this model's greatest strengths lie in recreating the inherent characteristics of the characters themselves and its relatively strong generalization capabilities, owing to its larger dataset. As such, this model is well-suited for tasks such as changing outfits, posing characters, and, of course, generating NSFW images of characters!😉".

For the following groups, it is not recommended to use this model and we express regret:

  1. Individuals who cannot tolerate any deviations from the original character design, even in the slightest detail.
  2. Individuals who are facing the application scenarios with high demands for accuracy in recreating character outfits.
  3. Individuals who cannot accept the potential randomness in AI-generated images based on the Stable Diffusion algorithm.
  4. Individuals who are not comfortable with the fully automated process of training character models using LoRA, or those who believe that training character models must be done purely through manual operations to avoid disrespecting the characters.
  5. Individuals who finds the generated image content offensive to their values.

items.name: Billions of Clothings - Extension for Billions of Characters
items.description:
IMPORTANT: This is an extension for the base wildcards of Billions of Characters.

With YAML-files you just get 1 nice wildcard-file Instead of 100 text files. They are human readable (best with Notepadd++) and they are easy to maintain.

You get the most of it, when all other Billions of Wildcards are present. I recommend at least Magic Chars, Cyberpunk or Scifi, since the premade prompt includes materials, which are not present in the base set.

Don't forget to leave a ❤️ to get a notification for future updates. ⭐ reviews are appreciated, too. Let me see what you created with this tool. ;)

note: Yaml files will throw isseus when using: "a1111-sd-webui-tagcomplete"extension. That's related to the extension, not the wildcards. An update fixed that already.

Usage

Unleash the full power:

Activate: Dynamic Prompts->Advanced Options->Unlink seed from prompt

Usage is pretty much the same as for "regular" wildcards.

You need the SD Dynamic Prompt Extension. Put the files directly into the wildcard folder:

~\stable-diffusion-webui\extensions\sd-dynamic-prompts\wildcards

They show up as a menu on the left in the Wildcards tab.

The YAML is structured and indented (that's how they work). Just with a little difference. You have to add the category layers in the wildcard.

Examples:

__BoCloth/random*__
__BoCloth/random-fullbody__
__BoCloth/random-upperbody__
__BoCloth/random-lowerbody__
__BoCloth/random-combination__
__BoCloth/random-extras__

Tip: A cool thing you can do, too, is using a wildcard "*" in the wildcards. So you could use the normal chararcter wildcards in the same prompt and get chars from both sets:

__BoChars*/female/classic__
__clothings*/female-attire__ # for clothings from all (installed) sets

This works the same way with all sets.

I made easy to use wildcards for character creations.

There are some wildcards that are not used for it. Have a look what's in there, too. You'll find a full list below. You can use each subcategory separately.

items.name: Mamen Mendizabal
items.description:
Mamen Mendizábal is a Spanish journalist and TV presenter.

This is a 140-step TI trained on a dataset of 15 images with these settings.

Curious about my work process? I have summarized it here.

Do you have a specific idea for a TI in mind? Visit my website and let me know.

Building a good prompt with my TIs

You're obviously free to experiment, but bear in mind that my TIs are trained with a more or less fixed phrasing, that normally starts with:

"photo of EMBEDDING_NAME, a woman"

So I recommend always starting your prompt like that and then building the rest of the prompt from there. For instance, "photo of beautiful (mamenmdz:0.99), a woman with beautiful hair, as a movie star in a (movie premiere), premiere gala, (near a movie theatre), natural skin texture, (elegant {red|yellow|blue|green|black|turquoise} sweater off-shoulder with suspenders), 24mm, 4k textures, soft cinematic light, adobe lightroom, photolab, hdr, intricate, elegant, highly detailed, sharp focus, ((((cinematic look)))), soothing tones, insane details, intricate details, hyperdetailed, low contrast, soft cinematic light, exposure blend, hdr, faded, (paparazzi in background), (painted lips:1.1), ((looking straight at the camera:1.1)), (smiling)"
